cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about improving neural machine translation (NMT) using word sense disambiguation (WSD). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as clustering algorithms and joint learning of word and sense vectors, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories as well. The paper also involves information retrieval techniques such as low-rank space representation, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves neural networks, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category as well.
